WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:06.900 --> 00:00:10.480
A world... Yes!

3
00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:16.530
A world for you who seek freedom stretches out right before your eyes.

4
00:00:16.530 --> 00:00:20.410
If you feel guided by endless dreams,

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:25.170
surpass them, flying the flag of your beliefs!

6
00:00:29.800 --> 00:00:35.480
I've just now begun to search, over the splashing waves

7
00:00:35.480 --> 00:00:38.630
For the everlasting world

8
00:00:39.930 --> 00:00:42.990
With this overflowing passion in my chest,

9
00:00:42.990 --> 00:00:45.070
I will go anywhere

10
00:00:45.070 --> 00:00:53.380
Seeking the light yet unseen

11
00:00:53.380 --> 00:00:58.940
When the summer sun stirs my heart's sails

12
00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:09.130
That's the signal to open the door to a new world

13
00:01:13.050 --> 00:01:18.060
Swaying on the waves, reaching beyond despair

14
00:01:18.060 --> 00:01:25.530
Aiming for the other side of the horizon

15
00:01:25.660 --> 00:01:31.330
I've just now begun to search, over the splashing waves

16
00:01:31.330 --> 00:01:34.510
For the everlasting world

17
00:01:35.950 --> 00:01:38.860
With this overflowing passion in my chest

18
00:01:38.860 --> 00:01:40.970
I will go anywhere

19
00:01:40.970 --> 00:01:47.560
Seeking the light yet unseen

20
00:01:49.710 --> 00:01:53.800
<b>Overture</b>

21
00:01:53.800 --> 00:01:55.720
I've gotta save him.
I've gotta save him!

22
00:01:55.720 --> 00:01:56.970
There are sky sharks!

23
00:01:58.850 --> 00:02:00.930
Consider this the wrath of God Enel!

24
00:02:01.350 --> 00:02:03.980
After all that, you were
no match for us priests.

25
00:02:03.980 --> 00:02:08.860
Sky Knight!

26
00:02:09.610 --> 00:02:12.700
You're a zoan, aren't you?!
Are you stupid?

27
00:02:17.620 --> 00:02:21.120
Oh, yeah, you're a zoan, too.

28
00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:23.750
Such an unfortunate weakness...

29
00:02:27.460 --> 00:02:30.170
Why don't you join your master?!

30
00:02:37.970 --> 00:02:39.430
How absurd!

31
00:02:39.430 --> 00:02:41.890
I can't stand how weak they all are.

32
00:02:42.640 --> 00:02:46.020
Were this river bottomless,
perhaps they'd stand a chance.

33
00:02:46.020 --> 00:02:49.480
Unfortunately for them,
there is a riverbed down there.

34
00:02:50.980 --> 00:02:52.490
Now then...

35
00:02:53.110 --> 00:02:56.700
I wonder if the three who escaped
have been hunted down yet.

36
00:02:59.740 --> 00:03:01.790
Is a well really all that strange?

37
00:03:01.790 --> 00:03:02.500
Yes.

38
00:03:03.120 --> 00:03:05.710
It's implausible for it to be
wedged under a tree.

39
00:03:06.670 --> 00:03:09.670
It's as if nature has
overtaken civilization here.

40
00:03:10.170 --> 00:03:13.630
Regardless, if we can't find
a way across this river,

41
00:03:14.170 --> 00:03:17.050
we won't be able
to get through the forest.

42
00:03:18.970 --> 00:03:21.600
Looks like finding that god
is out of the question.

43
00:03:21.600 --> 00:03:24.770
The civilization couldn't predict
the growth of this tree.

44
00:03:25.440 --> 00:03:27.520
I've never seen anything
quite like this.

45
00:03:28.060 --> 00:03:29.520
Hey, Nami!

46
00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:31.770
Can you see anything from up there?!

47
00:03:36.820 --> 00:03:40.240
The island where
a god lives, Upper Yard...

48
00:03:44.620 --> 00:03:46.910
Hey! What are you
mumbling up there?!

49
00:03:46.910 --> 00:03:48.830
Did you find that god?!

50
00:03:50.330 --> 00:03:52.170
I wonder if she saw something.

51
00:03:55.840 --> 00:03:57.220
This island...

52
00:03:57.220 --> 00:03:58.430
There's no way!

53
00:04:02.640 --> 00:04:04.430
You're basically finished.

54
00:04:04.430 --> 00:04:06.770
Hurry up and rest in peace.

55
00:04:06.770 --> 00:04:09.730
There's no way you can win
against a priest.

56
00:04:11.730 --> 00:04:13.360
I-I can't go on anymore!

57
00:04:13.360 --> 00:04:16.400
My heart can't take
any more surprises.

58
00:04:16.940 --> 00:04:19.450
You're all out of options.

59
00:04:20.950 --> 00:04:25.660
Your boat has nearly reached
the exit of the Lost Woods.

60
00:04:25.660 --> 00:04:28.040
When that happens, it's all over!

61
00:04:31.250 --> 00:04:34.340
Unless you learn to fly like a bird,

62
00:04:34.840 --> 00:04:36.840
you've got no chance of escape.

63
00:04:39.840 --> 00:04:44.680
You'll wander, lost in these woods,
until you die of exhaustion!

64
00:04:47.770 --> 00:04:49.020
That's not...

65
00:04:50.440 --> 00:04:52.190
gonna happen!

66
00:04:52.190 --> 00:04:53.690
Oh, but it will!

67
00:04:53.690 --> 00:04:55.570
Surprise Balls:

68
00:04:57.030 --> 00:04:58.900
Ball Dragon!

69
00:04:58.900 --> 00:05:01.240
Now let's have some fun!

70
00:05:02.370 --> 00:05:05.200
Which one is the firebomb ball?

71
00:05:05.200 --> 00:05:08.330
If you touch it, there will be
an extraordinary explosion!

72
00:05:13.420 --> 00:05:15.960
Good! Here's my chance.
We can still do this!

73
00:05:16.500 --> 00:05:18.630
I'll leave things here to you, Luffy!

74
00:05:24.550 --> 00:05:26.430
Climbing up that tree to escape?

75
00:05:26.430 --> 00:05:29.230
How can he read my mind?!

76
00:05:29.230 --> 00:05:30.890
Stop following me!

77
00:05:33.060 --> 00:05:34.270
Wh-What?!

78
00:05:36.570 --> 00:05:37.730
Oh, I see!

79
00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:41.400
It was controlled by this string.

80
00:05:41.400 --> 00:05:42.450
I'll take care...

81
00:05:43.870 --> 00:05:45.740
of this thing!

82
00:05:47.740 --> 00:05:50.450
I can't control
the Ball Dragon anymore!

83
00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:52.580
Such insolence!

84
00:05:52.580 --> 00:05:54.500
Just hang on and come to me!

85
00:06:00.340 --> 00:06:02.970
Hey, don't hang on
with the other hand, too!

86
00:06:23.530 --> 00:06:25.410
There it is!

87
00:06:25.410 --> 00:06:29.200
I was right! That's the exit,
no doubt about it!

88
00:06:29.700 --> 00:06:30.950
Of course!

89
00:06:30.950 --> 00:06:33.580
Why didn't I think of this earlier?!

90
00:06:33.580 --> 00:06:36.670
We fell from a high place,

91
00:06:37.130 --> 00:06:40.090
so of course the exit
is at the same height!

92
00:06:41.130 --> 00:06:44.380
Now that I know how to get out,
the boat rule doesn't matter!

93
00:06:44.760 --> 00:06:45.890
I have to hurry.

94
00:06:45.890 --> 00:06:48.010
I'm worried about that huge explosion.

95
00:06:48.010 --> 00:06:49.970
They'd better be okay!

96
00:06:49.970 --> 00:06:50.930
Ow, ow, ow, ow...

97
00:06:57.400 --> 00:06:58.900
That was close!

98
00:06:58.900 --> 00:07:01.030
What an unbelievable idiot!

99
00:07:01.030 --> 00:07:05.240
No, maybe he decided
to take me out with him.

100
00:07:05.240 --> 00:07:08.410
This isn't good.
My training is still insufficient!

101
00:07:08.410 --> 00:07:10.790
He completely took control
for a second there!

102
00:07:10.790 --> 00:07:13.830
If such a trivial thing
can break my focus,

103
00:07:14.330 --> 00:07:16.370
it'll hinder my mantra!

104
00:07:16.370 --> 00:07:17.790
You're right!

105
00:07:18.380 --> 00:07:19.590
That was close!

106
00:07:21.050 --> 00:07:23.210
You're still alive?!

107
00:07:24.340 --> 00:07:25.930
Get off of me!

108
00:07:25.930 --> 00:07:26.800
You idiot!

109
00:07:26.800 --> 00:07:28.640
Don't let him go, Luffy!
Get off of me!

110
00:07:28.640 --> 00:07:30.810
Hold on tight to that dango!

111
00:07:30.810 --> 00:07:31.640
You–

112
00:07:31.640 --> 00:07:33.720
Oh, Sanji! You're alive?!

113
00:07:33.720 --> 00:07:36.480
No thanks to you!

114
00:07:36.480 --> 00:07:38.270
Pay more attention to others!

115
00:07:38.940 --> 00:07:41.570
In any case, dango...

116
00:07:45.650 --> 00:07:48.410
You keep saying
"ordeal of this," "ordeal of that,"

117
00:07:48.410 --> 00:07:51.740
but frankly, we've done nothing
to earn this punishment.

118
00:07:51.740 --> 00:07:55.370
And yet, we're going through
this stupid sky ordeal...

119
00:07:55.370 --> 00:07:58.080
because two helpless ladies...

120
00:07:58.080 --> 00:08:00.210
are waiting for me
to come to their rescue.

121
00:08:01.210 --> 00:08:02.800
In other words...

122
00:08:04.800 --> 00:08:07.260
this is... the Ordeal of Love!

123
00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:09.260
Is this guy an idiot, too?!

124
00:08:10.010 --> 00:08:11.800
I said get off of me!

125
00:08:11.800 --> 00:08:15.890
Y-You! You!
Dammit! Let me go!

126
00:08:15.890 --> 00:08:18.730
Two against one is playing dirty!

127
00:08:22.110 --> 00:08:24.690
You bastards kidnapped our friends.

128
00:08:25.230 --> 00:08:29.200
You made a cute angel cry
and tried to kill her.

129
00:08:29.200 --> 00:08:31.820
You have no right
to say we play dirty.

130
00:08:31.820 --> 00:08:33.450
He's right, you know.

131
00:08:33.450 --> 00:08:37.200
It's amazing that you can
predict our movements,

132
00:08:37.200 --> 00:08:39.330
but even so...

133
00:08:39.330 --> 00:08:42.710
it doesn't mean anything
if you can't avoid our attacks, right?

134
00:08:44.250 --> 00:08:45.880
I-Idiots! Stop it!

135
00:08:45.880 --> 00:08:48.130
I'm one of the priests that serve God!

136
00:08:48.130 --> 00:08:48.970
Let me go!

137
00:08:48.970 --> 00:08:50.220
Hey, are you listening?!

138
00:08:50.220 --> 00:08:55.430
Avoiding a priest's judgment
is a first-degree crime in Skypiea!

139
00:08:55.430 --> 00:08:58.180
Listen to me!

140
00:08:58.180 --> 00:09:02.150
Attacking me is a declaration of war
against the almighty God Enel!

141
00:09:02.150 --> 00:09:04.820
Keep your mouth shut,
or the flavor will escape!

142
00:09:06.150 --> 00:09:10.150
When you prepare pepper for
the ultimate mignonette sauce,

143
00:09:13.410 --> 00:09:16.700
the most important step
is to strongly, roughly...

144
00:09:17.370 --> 00:09:20.120
and without hesitation
crush it into a fine powder.

145
00:09:25.040 --> 00:09:28.460
Then, the sublime flavor
confined inside will be...

146
00:09:29.220 --> 00:09:31.470
Stop it!

147
00:09:32.640 --> 00:09:34.220
Stop it!

148
00:09:34.220 --> 00:09:36.810
Stop it! It's gonna hurt! So stop it!

149
00:09:39.390 --> 00:09:41.770
Concassé!

150
00:09:49.990 --> 00:09:54.200
Gan Fall, the former god,
went into Upper Yard.

151
00:10:07.090 --> 00:10:08.880
What's the matter, Aisa?

152
00:10:09.460 --> 00:10:11.220
Two voices went silent.

153
00:10:11.220 --> 00:10:12.380
What'd you say?!

154
00:10:13.550 --> 00:10:14.840
Is that your mantra?

155
00:10:14.840 --> 00:10:15.800
Yeah...

156
00:10:15.800 --> 00:10:18.350
Just now...

157
00:10:20.930 --> 00:10:24.770
You can tell with your mantra, Aisa?

158
00:10:24.770 --> 00:10:27.020
Two voices went quiet...

159
00:10:27.020 --> 00:10:28.230
Is that true?!

160
00:10:31.070 --> 00:10:32.570
There's no mistake about it.

161
00:10:32.570 --> 00:10:36.530
You all know that since birth,
she's been able to use mantra,

162
00:10:36.530 --> 00:10:40.160
a mysterious power that
allows her to sense people

163
00:10:40.160 --> 00:10:41.950
even from a distance.

164
00:10:43.080 --> 00:10:45.330
So two voices have gone silent?

165
00:10:45.330 --> 00:10:47.670
Yes... They disappeared
around the same time...

166
00:10:48.420 --> 00:10:51.960
I think... Gan Fall
and one of the priests...

167
00:10:51.960 --> 00:10:52.760
A mutual kill?!

168
00:10:52.760 --> 00:10:54.840
A good performance
from the old man!

169
00:10:54.840 --> 00:10:56.510
That leaves three priests.

170
00:10:56.510 --> 00:10:58.220
This works in our favor.

171
00:10:59.100 --> 00:11:03.100
Looks like heaven
has answered our prayers.

172
00:11:04.230 --> 00:11:07.900
This is our chance
to crush the priests.

173
00:11:07.900 --> 00:11:09.480
Yeah!

174
00:11:09.480 --> 00:11:13.400
We'll launch an all-out attack
on Upper Yard immediately!

175
00:11:13.400 --> 00:11:15.030
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

176
00:11:18.570 --> 00:11:23.000
You'll always be nervous
around Wyper, huh?

177
00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:24.960
C'mon, out of the way.

178
00:11:24.120 --> 00:11:24.960
Ow!

179
00:11:26.790 --> 00:11:28.540
Hey, Raki! Wait!

180
00:11:29.170 --> 00:11:30.130
What is it?

181
00:11:30.130 --> 00:11:32.590
Gan Fall didn't beat that priest.

182
00:11:32.960 --> 00:11:36.300
There are other people here.
They did it.

183
00:11:36.300 --> 00:11:37.890
Other people?

184
00:11:37.890 --> 00:11:40.640
Was it those Blue Sea dwellers
who entered Skypiea?

185
00:11:40.640 --> 00:11:43.640
I don't know,
but they're definitely scary!

186
00:11:44.140 --> 00:11:44.980
So...

187
00:11:45.430 --> 00:11:46.390
be careful.

188
00:11:48.520 --> 00:11:50.060
Got it.

189
00:11:50.060 --> 00:11:52.730
Aisa, give me your bag.

190
00:11:52.730 --> 00:11:53.440
What?!

191
00:11:53.440 --> 00:11:57.910
No! This is my secret bag
with my treasure inside!

192
00:11:57.910 --> 00:11:59.160
I know.

193
00:12:02.080 --> 00:12:04.910
I'll get some more for you.

194
00:12:04.910 --> 00:12:06.370
Really?!

195
00:12:05.660 --> 00:12:06.370
Yeah.

196
00:12:18.510 --> 00:12:19.510
Huh?

197
00:12:20.340 --> 00:12:23.430
I've been rescued?

198
00:12:25.890 --> 00:12:27.730
Sky Knight!

199
00:12:27.730 --> 00:12:30.020
We need a doctor! Wait, that's me!

200
00:12:33.150 --> 00:12:35.400
Thank goodness... He's still alive.

201
00:12:37.860 --> 00:12:40.070
This is strange, though.

202
00:12:40.070 --> 00:12:43.240
I thought we fell into that river.

203
00:12:43.240 --> 00:12:45.450
I wonder who pulled us out...

204
00:12:48.330 --> 00:12:49.960
Who's there? Did someone say "god"?

205
00:12:50.460 --> 00:12:52.380
Who just spoke?!

206
00:13:03.220 --> 00:13:04.850
Huh? What?!

207
00:13:14.230 --> 00:13:18.190
Spit it out already!
What did you see up there?!

208
00:13:18.190 --> 00:13:20.240
No more questions. Just follow me!

209
00:13:20.240 --> 00:13:22.200
We have to reach the shore somehow.

210
00:13:23.410 --> 00:13:25.410
Hey! Give me a hand!

211
00:13:25.410 --> 00:13:28.830
How can we follow you
if you're behind us?!

212
00:13:28.830 --> 00:13:29.750
The shore?

213
00:13:29.750 --> 00:13:30.910
That's right.

214
00:13:30.910 --> 00:13:33.670
We need to verify it up close.

215
00:13:36.670 --> 00:13:40.670
I'm starting to doubt my own eyes...

216
00:13:41.220 --> 00:13:43.470
I thought he'd never shut up.

217
00:13:43.470 --> 00:13:45.140
Hey!

218
00:13:45.140 --> 00:13:48.180
Luffy! Sanji! I found the boat!

219
00:13:48.180 --> 00:13:51.440
Hurry up! Or it'll leave the forest!

220
00:13:51.940 --> 00:13:54.310
Oh, Usopp's alive.

221
00:13:54.310 --> 00:13:56.940
Wait, he said the boat's leaving!

222
00:13:57.360 --> 00:13:58.400
Oh, crap!

223
00:13:58.860 --> 00:14:02.150
It's almost to the stretch
that leads to the exit!

224
00:14:03.450 --> 00:14:05.660
Get over here
and hold on to me!

225
00:14:05.660 --> 00:14:06.620
Hold on to you?

226
00:14:06.620 --> 00:14:07.620
Here goes!

227
00:14:08.120 --> 00:14:08.830
Usopp...

228
00:14:08.830 --> 00:14:14.210
Aah-eeh-ah-eeh-aaaaah-eeh-ah-eeh-aaaah!

229
00:14:19.170 --> 00:14:20.840
All right! I got it!

230
00:14:20.840 --> 00:14:23.590
Yahoo! Usopp's the man!

231
00:14:23.590 --> 00:14:26.640
That hurt! Are you trying to kill me?!

232
00:14:26.640 --> 00:14:27.600
I got excited!

233
00:14:27.600 --> 00:14:29.220
You're pretty cool sometimes!

234
00:14:29.220 --> 00:14:31.770
Yeah! You underestimated me,
didn't you?!

235
00:14:31.770 --> 00:14:32.480
Huh?

236
00:14:32.980 --> 00:14:34.060
Huh? Huh?
Hey! Hey, hey!

237
00:14:34.060 --> 00:14:36.610
Hey! W-W-Wait a second!

238
00:14:47.320 --> 00:14:49.200
No... No biggie...

239
00:14:49.200 --> 00:14:51.450
I'll make you pay for this...

240
00:14:51.450 --> 00:14:56.170
It would have been easier
for me to stretch here myself...

241
00:14:57.580 --> 00:15:01.800
Anyway, we're almost free
of the Lost Woods.

242
00:15:06.260 --> 00:15:08.680
So Satori has fallen...

243
00:15:09.430 --> 00:15:12.640
What a rookie,
letting his mantra falter!

244
00:15:13.230 --> 00:15:16.560
I believe the illegal entrants
are from the Blue Sea this time.

245
00:15:16.560 --> 00:15:18.980
It seems they're no ordinary people.

246
00:15:18.980 --> 00:15:21.530
The sacrifices are
roaming free as well...

247
00:15:21.530 --> 00:15:23.690
However, even if we let them be,

248
00:15:23.690 --> 00:15:26.450
they won't manage
to find a way off the island.

249
00:15:28.070 --> 00:15:29.870
More importantly, now...

250
00:15:32.040 --> 00:15:36.540
<b>"Sky Punk" Gedatsu
Skypiean Priest</b>

251
00:15:40.500 --> 00:15:43.710
Do you sense the voice of
a sorrowful warrior, Holy?

252
00:15:44.720 --> 00:15:47.260
No matter how many battles,
it's the same result.

253
00:15:48.010 --> 00:15:52.060
Shura defeated Gan Fall,
but the Ordeal of Balls was overcome.

254
00:15:52.640 --> 00:15:55.390
Such a tumultuous day!

255
00:15:56.310 --> 00:15:58.020
They shall not pass.

256
00:15:58.020 --> 00:16:00.480
Even attempting to see God
is pure insolence.

257
00:16:01.480 --> 00:16:05.320
Though it's nearly sunset,
it seems Upper Yard is going to be...

258
00:16:05.320 --> 00:16:09.820
<b>"Sky Breeder" Ohm
Skypiean Priest</b>

259
00:16:07.610 --> 00:16:09.820
quite shaken up.

260
00:16:09.820 --> 00:16:19.290
<b>"Sky Rider" Shura
Skypiean Priest</b>

261
00:16:12.030 --> 00:16:14.830
The fugitives can wait.

262
00:16:14.830 --> 00:16:19.290
It seems some opponents
deserving of my wrath have appeared.

263
00:16:43.270 --> 00:16:45.650
Listen up, everyone!

264
00:16:45.650 --> 00:16:48.780
Upper Yard is in chaos right now!

265
00:16:48.780 --> 00:16:51.490
This is the opportunity of a lifetime!

266
00:16:51.820 --> 00:16:54.790
We're heading straight
for God's Shrine!

267
00:16:55.370 --> 00:16:57.700
Do not fear Enel!

268
00:16:58.410 --> 00:17:03.420
Our savior, the almighty Kalgara,
shall preserve us!

269
00:17:03.920 --> 00:17:06.050
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

270
00:17:06.050 --> 00:17:07.130
Braham!

271
00:17:07.130 --> 00:17:07.920
Yeah!

272
00:17:07.920 --> 00:17:08.920
Kamakiri!

273
00:17:09.880 --> 00:17:10.630
Genbo!

274
00:17:10.630 --> 00:17:11.760
Yeah!

275
00:17:11.760 --> 00:17:12.640
Raki!

276
00:17:12.640 --> 00:17:13.760
Yeah!

277
00:17:13.760 --> 00:17:15.310
Make it back safe!

278
00:17:15.310 --> 00:17:16.640
We're splitting up here!

279
00:17:21.350 --> 00:17:25.820
We swear to the great warrior Kalgara
to shine the Light of Shandora!

280
00:17:25.820 --> 00:17:28.030
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

281
00:17:31.700 --> 00:17:34.740
– So you've come, Shandians!
– So you've come, Shandians!

282
00:17:41.290 --> 00:17:43.960
There's no need to explain, is there?

283
00:17:44.460 --> 00:17:45.920
Look at this.

284
00:17:47.000 --> 00:17:48.550
You recognize this, right?

285
00:17:49.510 --> 00:17:51.220
What's going on?!

286
00:17:51.220 --> 00:17:53.390
How did something
from below get up here?

287
00:17:53.890 --> 00:17:55.220
That's the same one, right?

288
00:17:55.220 --> 00:17:56.350
No, it's not.

289
00:17:56.350 --> 00:17:57.310
What?!

290
00:17:57.310 --> 00:18:00.100
This is the other half
of the one we saw on the ground.

291
00:18:00.100 --> 00:18:01.310
The other half?!

292
00:18:01.310 --> 00:18:03.690
It's been bothering me all along.

293
00:18:03.690 --> 00:18:07.110
This kind of land shouldn't exist
in the White-White Sea.

294
00:18:07.690 --> 00:18:12.860
From the start, it was strange
that this island wasn't made of island clouds.

295
00:18:12.860 --> 00:18:16.490
In other words,
the island of Upper Yard...

296
00:18:17.780 --> 00:18:20.160
originated on the surface below.

297
00:18:21.120 --> 00:18:23.670
That house seemed strange to me.

298
00:18:23.670 --> 00:18:30.420
There was a second floor,
but no stairs to reach it.

299
00:18:30.420 --> 00:18:33.470
Plus, there's no reason
to build a house on the water's edge.

300
00:18:34.300 --> 00:18:37.550
That seashore
was a split in the island!

301
00:18:38.930 --> 00:18:41.140
A-Amazing!

302
00:18:41.140 --> 00:18:43.060
Idiots! Look closer.

303
00:18:43.060 --> 00:18:45.060
A dreamer, huh?

304
00:18:45.060 --> 00:18:48.020
He's dreamt up quite
the appearance, at least.

305
00:18:48.020 --> 00:18:48.690
Why?

306
00:18:48.690 --> 00:18:51.990
What the...?! It's just a board?!

307
00:18:57.160 --> 00:19:01.370
This is the other half of that island
that was torn away.

308
00:19:03.460 --> 00:19:06.290
This island was part of Jaya!

309
00:19:08.540 --> 00:19:12.630
So the island was split in two
a long time ago,

310
00:19:12.630 --> 00:19:15.090
and part of it rose into the sky.

311
00:19:17.890 --> 00:19:21.010
But how could something 
like that happen?!

312
00:19:22.390 --> 00:19:25.640
There are so many south birds...

313
00:19:25.640 --> 00:19:27.440
But why...

314
00:19:27.940 --> 00:19:30.480
Why are they so big?!

315
00:19:49.960 --> 00:19:51.920
Hey! It's about time you woke up!

316
00:19:53.050 --> 00:19:54.630
Is it morning already?

317
00:19:56.840 --> 00:19:58.220
That's just like Zoro!

318
00:19:59.050 --> 00:20:00.930
Stay focused, dumbasses!

319
00:20:06.850 --> 00:20:08.810
The "City of Gold" that Noland saw...

320
00:20:09.440 --> 00:20:12.150
that once existed on the surface...

321
00:20:12.150 --> 00:20:14.400
It didn't sink into the ocean!

322
00:20:16.450 --> 00:20:17.820
This part of Jaya...

323
00:20:19.070 --> 00:20:20.950
has been in the sky all this time!
